'We actually won the lottery when it came to dwarfism,' Mr Coleman admitted. 'Ken and Darien specially chose for us the one who was the least obviously affected but we were prepared to have a pretty ugly, little dog.'

John said the Northcotes were completely upfront and forthcoming with the challenges they would face having a dog with dwarfism.

